experimental model techniques and equipment for flutter investigations. an outline is given of the uses of flutter models as an aid to the designer in the avoidance of flutter. details are given of the different types and methods of construction that are used for flutter models and of the various test facilities that are available for high speed and low speed tests. the procedure followed in the u.k. for flutter clearance of the full scale aircraft is described, and the value of the electronic flutter simulator in this field is discussed.